      <h2 class="title">
      <a href="/content/best-cake-ever" title="Best. Cake. Ever.">Best. Cake. Ever.</a>
    </h2>
  
  

  
      <div class="meta">
              <div class="submitted">
		By <a href="/users/katherine-druckman" title="View user profile.">Katherine Druckman</a>&nbsp;<!--|
		Dec 18, 2013 -->
     
      
              <div class="terms terms-inline"><ul class="links inline"><li class="taxonomy_term_916 first"><a href="/tag/cake" rel="tag" title="">Cake</a></li>
<li class="taxonomy_term_405"><a href="/tag/fun" rel="tag" title="">fun</a></li>
<li class="taxonomy_term_915 last"><a href="/tag/reddit" rel="tag" title="">Reddit</a></li>
</ul></div>
      
  	 </div>
    </div>
  
  
    


  <div class="content">

    
    
            
                    <a href="/content/best-cake-ever" class="imagecache imagecache-teaser imagecache-linked imagecache-teaser_linked"></a>        
        

<p>Redditor <a href="http://www.reddit.com/user/azimir">azimir</a> <a href="http://www.reddit.com/r/linux/comments/1t6h2a/when_my_mother_asked_for_a_linux_cake_she_had_no/">submitted a photo of his birthday cake to reddit</a>, and I couldn't help but share with the whole class. From the comments, I gather that the baker's son is a Linux geek and hooked him up with some code to decorate the cake.<span class="read-more"><a href="/content/best-cake-ever"> more>></a></span>
